%I A394465 #13 Mar 31 2026 08:55:07
%S A394465 1,1,4,6,6,18,54,124,234,574,1748,4514
%N A394465 Number of graceful Prüfer codes on n vertices whose tree is the path graph and whose last element equals 1.
%C A394465 Any labeled tree on n vertices admits a unique Prüfer code. A graceful labeling of a tree on n vertices assigns the labels {0,1,...,n-1} to the vertices such that the induced edge labels (absolute differences of endpoint labels) are exactly {1,2,...,n-1}.
%C A394465 A path graph on n vertices is a tree with exactly two vertices of degree 1 and all other vertices of degree 2.
%D A394465 Douglas B. West, Introduction to Graph Theory, Pearson Education Pte. Ltd, 2002, page 81.
%H A394465 Igor Blokhin, <a href="https://github.com/IgorBlokhin/Graph_Theory">Graph Theory</a> (Python repository).
%F A394465 For n>=4: a(n) = A112362(n) - A394464(n).
%e A394465 a(4)=1, meaning that among all graceful Prüfer codes (of length 2) of path graph on vertices {0,1,2,3}, there are 1 code ending in 1: (3, 1). This code correspond to the graph 0--3--1--2.
%Y A394465 Cf. A112362, A394464.
%K A394465 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A394465 4,3
%A A394465 _Igor Blokhin_, Mar 21 2026
